Thank you Michel, for your very gracious 'withdrawal' from the ranks of the
whiners about Frontier. Yes, Frontier does have its bugs, but they are all
more irritant than fatal and are mostly avoidable. I have a couple to report
myself through Dino, but I also know how to avoid them. Frontier is still an
incredible achievement and one of my sons has now had a superb introduction
to the physics of spaceflight and knowledge of our Solar System, besides
enjoying himself thoroughly (the best spent $38 in a long time). 

Guys (and gals), or gentlemen and ladies (for the world outside the US),
let us use all use somewhat less of the net bandwidth in <destructive>
criticism of Frontier. Factually document the bugs ( including the version
number of the executable, and whether it is the Amiga or IBM version !) and
send them to Dino Dini (amiga@hosta.dircon.co.uk). Obviously, feel free to
document them here too......

David Braben has spent several years of his life putting Frontier together; I
am certain that he will upgrade the program to remove the most irritating
bugs and will make it available publicly somehow. If I were he, I would wait
a little while to allow *ALL OF US Frontier users* to complete OUR beta-tests
before executing the update.

John Lewis

