Someone wrote :

+ Also, I was just wondering... In Elite (the 8 bit version),
+ Military lasers weren't always the best. Mining lasers worked
+ best against Thargoids. Has anyone tried this in Frontier.

	I used to use mining lasers in Elite on the Spectrum and BBC versions,
and found them to be highly effective. Generally 3-4 hits would wipe out any
opposition, and they rarely overheated. In the immortal words of SMASH TV, 
"Total Carnage! I love it!"

	Last night I got around to trying them out in Frontier. I loaded up a
Cobra Mark I (which for some reason I've taken a liking to) with various
components, and mounted one of these on the bow. The idea was to find an
unstable system and see how various configurations worked.

	The result, well I died.... Violently.

	Currently my accuracy with lasers is rather low, and I tend to find
that I cannot hit with anything short of a beam laser. The mining lasers seem
to have a very small zone of effect, and I could have sworn that I was aiming
dead center on the Osprey as it approached me. The other problem is that they
overheat within 5 shots.

	What I think may be a good use for them though is to turret mount one
on a larger vessel, eg the Tiger, and have a 4MW mounted in the front position.
Then, when you come up against a well shielded foe, shoot it with the mining
laser to reduce shields before going in for the kill.

	Graeme

