Guess what - another bug. (Forget all this talk about an alt.games.frontier group - a stupid idea if I ever heard one - and just create alt.bugs.frontier instead, or even alt.games.frontier.bugs.bugs.and.more.bugs). Anyway, this one has to do with the MB4
 Mining Machines. I don't think anyone's reported it yet.

Buy one MB4 - fine, no problem. It's when you own more than one at the same time that you start to run into problems. I discovered when returning to the planet on which all three of my rigs were set up that - due to my being slightly too accurate when try
ing to land near to my second rig - the game gurus if a rig is destroyed (so I crashed into the thing. Could happen to anyone). Later, I also discovered that it ALSO gurus if you try to sell a rig, or sell a ship with a rig on it.

All is not lost, however. If you're trying to get rid of your rigs, it turns out that you can safely destroy the last rig on the list (or sell it, if you've only got one rig left). The best thing to do is set all your rigs down on a planet, target the las
t one on the list and proceed to shoot them all in REVERSE ORDER. When you're left with only one, you can then either safely pick it up and sell it (usually not worth the effort) or just blow that one off the face of the planet too.

Suggestion: it's time for David Braben to speak. Maybe some of you who know him (I believe Dino Dini mentioned that he did) could ask him HOW COME FRONTIER WAS RELEASED IN THIS SORRY STATE?? And post his answer to the group?

